#Text=James Altham
#Text=Sir James Altham ( died 1617 ) was an English judge .
#Text=Early life
#Text=Altham was descended from Christopher Altham of Girlington , in the West Riding of Yorkshire .

#Text=He was the third son of James Altham of Mark Hall , Latton , in Essex , Sheriff of London in 1557 – 58 , and sheriff of Essex in 1570 , by Elizabeth Blancke , daughter of Thomas Blancke of London , Haberdasher , and sister of Sir Thomas Blanke , who was Lord Mayor of London in 1583 .
#Text=Altham was educated at Trinity College , Cambridge , entered Gray 's Inn in 1575 and was called to the bar in 1581 .
#Text=He is mentioned in Croke 's reports for the first time as arguing a case in the Queen 's Bench in 1587 .
#Text=In 1589 he was elected M.P. for Bramber in Sussex .
#Text=He was knighted in 1605 . [ 1 ]
#Text=Legal career
#Text=He was appointed reader at Gray 's Inn in 1600 , and in 1603 double reader ( duplex lector ) .
#Text=In the same year he was made serjeant-at-law .
#Text=In 1606 he was appointed one of the barons of the exchequer , in succession to Sir J. Savile , and knighted .

#Text=In 1610 , a question having arisen concerning the power of the crown to impose restrictions on trade and industry by proclamation , the two chief justices , the chief baron , and Baron Altham were appointed to consider the matter .
#Text=The result of their consultation was that they unanimously resolved " that the king by his proclamation cannot create any offence which was not an offence before ...

#Text=Altham died on 21 February 1617 , and the lord keeper , Sir Francis Bacon , in appointing his successor , characterised the late baron as  one of the gravest and most reverend of the judges of this kingdom . "

column1: #Text=He was buried in Oxhey Chapel , built by himself on his estate at Oxhey in Hertfordshire , where a monument still preserves his memory and that of his third wife , who died on 21 April 1638 .
#Text=Family life
#Text=By his first wife , Margaret , daughter of Oliver Skinner , Altham had issue one child only , a son James , afterwards Sir James Altham of Oxhey , knight .
#Text=This Sir James Altham married Elizabeth , daughter of Sir Richard Sutton of London , and had issue a boy , who died in infancy , and two daughters , Elizabeth and Frances .

#Text=Elizabeth Altham married Arthur Annesley , 1st Earl of Anglesey , second Viscount Valentia and first Earl of Anglesey , whose second son , Altham Annesley , was created in 1680 Baron Altham of Altham , with limitation in default of male issue to his younger brothers .
#Text=His only son dying in infancy , the title devolved upon the younger branch of the Annesley family , who subsequently succeeded to the earldom of Anglesey .
#Text=The earldom lapsed in 1771 , when the English House of Lords decided against the legitimacy of the last claimant .
#Text=Frances , the second daughter of Sir James Altham of Oxhey , married Richard Vaughan , 2nd Earl of Carbery .
#Text=The title lapsed in 1713 .
#Text=By his second wife , Mary , daughter of Richard Stapers , Esq. , Altham had three children , a son Richard , who died without issue ; two daughters , Elizabeth and Mary .

#Text=Elizabeth married first Sir Francis Astley of Hill Morton and Melton , knight , then Robert Digby , 1st Baron Digby ( c. 1599 – 1642 ) ( Irish peerage ) , and lastly Sir Robert Bernard , 1st Baronet , serjeant-at-law .
#Text=Mary married Sir Francis Stydolph ( d. 1655 ) and was the mother of Sir Richard Stydolph , Baronet . [ 2 ]
#Text=By his third wife , Helen Saunderson , Altham had no children .
#Text=Robert Altham , currently a circuit judge is one of his descendants . [ 3 ]
